(83, 'X-Cricket', 'Cricket: Not a Game, It\'s an Emotion!????', 3, 'Ravi Sanghani', 9726978401, 0, 400, '8', 3000, 2000, 0, 'mechanical and it department gap', '20 Feb 2025, 21 Feb 2025', 'This will be played as gully cricketthere will be 8 players in the team some rules will be explained at the time of the game', 'Gully cricket rule will be implemented in this gameAll the rules are very basic,competitive, and also give excitement to the playersThe rules will be explained before the game start (for every teams)', 'Elimination 1', 'total winner of the first round will play next day', 'Second elimination(Super 10)', 'Same as the first day', 'Final round', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 1, 1),
(84, 'X-Antakshari', 'Melodies, Memories, Fun, Together!', 9, 'Prof Vishal Kothari / Prof. Riya Patel', 9427776727, 0, 150, '3', 1500, 1000, 0, 'class room 101', '20-02-2025', 'Antakshari, (????????? the game of the ending letter) is a spoken parlor game. Each contestant sings the first verse of a song (often Classical Hindustani or Bollywood songs) that begins with the consonant of Hindi alphabet on which the previous contestant\'s song ended.', '1.Three participants per team.2.All Rounds are compulsory.3.Team coordination is must.4.Only one member form the team should give answer. Later members can join in singing.5.There will be four rounds of different modes.6.In case of a tie there shall be a fifth round.7.Internal communication can be done between team members.8.External storage devices, laptops, any paper material, mobile are not allowed.9.College proof is necessary (ID card) during the event.10.The decision taken by the organizers will be considered as final.', 'Geet Gata Chal', '1.Simple Antakshari among the groups will be played.2.15 second time limit will be given to start a song.3.Ten mark for each right song. 4.No negative marking in this round.5.Five marks for correct recognition after pass.', 'Sargam', '1.This will be an audio buzzer round, based on Hindi film songs.2.The signature tune of a song will be played on the audio player for about ten seconds. 3.The participants will have to recognize the song correctly and sing the mukhda of the song within 5 seconds after hitting the buzzer.4.The team which hits the buzzer first will get to sing the song. 5.There would be 5 audio clues.6.Twenty marks for the right answer.7.Minus ten for not singing the song in the specified time, after hitting the buzzer. 8.Ten marks for correct recognition after pass.', 'Mein hoon Kaun', '1.This will be an Image/Video round, based on Hindi film.2.One poster/clip of movie will be shown.3.You have to identify the movie and sing a song of that movie.4.Ten marks for the right Movie Name.5.Ten marks for the song of this Movie. 6.Minus Ten for wrong identifying movie or song .7.Five marks for correct recognition after pass.', 'Shabd Jaal', '1.One participant would have to come to the dais and pick one chit from a bowl containing chits bearing names of different Words.2.One word would be given to each team and that team would have to sing songs, based on the given word. 3.The given word must come in the first four lines.4.Twenty mark for each right song. 5.Minus ten negative marking in this round.6.Five marks for correct recognition after pass.', 'Tie Breaker Round', '1.If there is a tie among the teams, a fifth round will have to be played.2.It would be surprised round.3.Explanation would be given on the fly.', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 1, 1),
(85, 'X-Probe Competition', 'Sa Vidya Ya Vimuktaye', 9, 'Prof.Kalpesh Patel,Prof.Monika Patel', 7862865307, 50, 0, '1', 1500, 1000, 500, 'Classroom 102', '20-02-2025', 'This is one type of quiz in which participants need to give answer to General knowledge of IT fields question.', 'only 1 participants allowed.', 'Elimination round: Knowledge Matters', 'In this round Participants need to give online quiz by their mobile, we will provide the id and password for the same at run time. We will be asking ten questions in this round. Students who give maximum right answer in minimum time are selected in this round. Total 10 students are selected through this round. Selected Students will be played Competition but this competition are played in a group of two so we will make one draw among this ten students and select a pair of two for each team. For competition round, five team will be selected through this round.', 'Storm Your Brain', 'In this round we are going to ask 2 Question to each team,10 marks for right answer and no negative marking for 1st round.30 seconds time will be given for each question.', 'Thirst for knowledge', 'In this round participants are going to answer question and whomever know the answer can raise their hand and give the answer if given answer is right ,they will be getting +20 mark if answer is wrong they will be getting -20 marks, total 10 question are available in this round.', 'FINAL ROUND- \"Gyan Hi Sarvasva Hai\"', 'In this final round those 2 teams having maximum marks among 4 teams are eligible to play this final round, another 2 teams will be eliminated from here.2 selected teams will be played this final round. We will ask 10 questions and each right answer having +50 marks and each wrong answer having -25 marks.', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 6, 1),
(86, 'X-Stall Zone', 'One Stop with More Flavours-Every bite and Everyplace is filled with Love', 8, 'Shah Abhi Hirenkumar', 9104596941, 0, 250, '1-5', 3000, 2000, 1000, 'LDRP-ITR Outside Arc Corridor', '20 Feb 2025, 21 Feb 2025', 'The participants will be given a 6X6 stall with two tables, chair and one electrical point. The participants may sell products like food items /electronics/ art/tattoos/ Mehendi or any other products. No fire based stoves or gas stoves will be allowed. You may bring induction stove or microwave oven and extension boards. The participants should inform the details of products during registration, Approval of products and stalls are reserved with the event coordinator.', '• Every Participant has to come in a team of maximum 5 persons. • Should report at 8.50 am on 20rd Feb 2025 at Room No. 202 for stall allotment.• You are responsible for the infrastructure and materials provided to you. You have to return the resources provided at the end of the event. In case of any damage, you will be penalized for the same.• Only the participants should stay inside the stall. No outsiders are allowed.• Quality and Hygiene should be given top priority. Any compromise on this will lead to disqualification.• Mineral water should be used to prepare the food stuff at your stall.• The teams should keep the surroundings of their stall neat and clean.• Electricity will be provided inside the stall (one socket). Participants may bring one extension box.• Any kind of indiscipline /violence / malpractice are prohibited, and if found guilty, that team would be immediately disqualified from the game.• The judgement of the event is totally unbiased. All the rights reserved with the coordinators. Any argument / violation of rule will lead to disqualification without any justification', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 5, 1),
(87, 'X- Brix N Bond', 'brix', 6, 'Mr. Vikas Bhavsar', 9409569325, 0, 100, '2', 1000, 500, 250, 'Building Construction lab, Ground floor, Shift 2 building', '20-02-2025', '', '• Number of participants per team will be one or two.• No electronic devices are allowed.• Blocks will be provided from the college.• There may be two rounds if number of participated team is more than 6.• Time limit is applied for both rounds.• Participants are not required to do any prior preparation for masonry bond.• Selection of type of Masonry bond will be at time of Event.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 3, 1),
(88, 'X- Clue Zone', 'Success with Senses. Smell, Taste & Touch to Triumph.', 8, 'Ravrani bharvi Tusharbhai', 9313612382, 50, 0, '1', 1500, 1000, 500, 'Room No. 201', '20-02-2025', 'Use your senses to identify the products or brands. There will be challenges for all your senses.. Hearing, Seeing, Tasting, Smelling and Touching. Blindfolded, the participants will rely on their senses to identity the product or brand, as asked.', 'Individual participation.', '', '• Hearing and seeing senses will be tested. There will be elimination after this round.', '', '• Individual Participation.• Participant will be blind folded.• Products will be given/presented to them to touch, smell and taste. • Participant should write/inform the brand name/product name as instructed. • No one should talk or discuss anything with anyone.• The judgement of the event is totally unbiased. All the rights reserved with the coordinators. Any argument / violation of rule will lead to disqualification without any justification', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 5, 1),
(89, 'X-ROBORACE', '\"Where innovation races to win\"', 3, 'Robo Rebels', 8780573147, 0, 150, '3', 6000, 4000, 2000, 'Shift -2', '20 Feb 2025, 21 Feb 2025', 'Build a manual wire/wireless bot which can surpass all obstacles and hurdles on its way and reach the final line in minimum time', '( Round-1) Race up to check point with minimum time period.(Round-2) Complete full Track Race with minimum time period.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 3, 1),
(90, 'X-Treasure Hunt Zone', 'Mysteries Overloaded', 8, 'Mehul Mavjibhai Prajapati', 9726471082, 0, 250, '5', 3000, 2000, 1000, 'Room No. 202', '20-02-2025', 'Participants have to decode clues, overcome challenging tasks within a given time to find out or uncover hidden treasures. Each clue leads to the next location and after around 10 clues, participants will get the final treasure. The team which brings the final treasure will be the winner. In case of any discrepancy, the judgement will be based on thinking skills, team collaboration, team discipline etc.', '• Every Participant has to come in a team of 5 persons.• Should report at 10.30 am on 20rd Feb 2025 at Room No. 202 for instructions and preliminary round, in case of more groups registered. For final treasure hunt, only 10 teams will be selected. But the preliminary round too will be equally interesting.• Any kind of indiscipline /violence / malpractice is prohibited, and if found guilty, that team would be immediately disqualified from the game. While searching clues, participants have to take care of the institute property. Any damage for the property is punishable with penalty and will be informed to the parent organization.• The judgement of the event is totally unbiased. All the rights reserved with the coordinators. Any argument / violation of rule will lead to disqualification without any justification', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 5, 1),
(91, 'X-Insta Influencer Zone', 'Create Influence, Be Influencer.', 8, 'Nayankumar Rameshbhai Vaghela', 8128900301, 50, 0, '1', 1500, 1000, 500, 'NA', '20 Feb 2025, 21 Feb 2025', 'Participants should make an Advertisement video / Promotional video / Documentary film for 1 minute covering any one of the stalls (of stall zone competition Established on the day of the event. Further Instructions will be given in the WhatsApp group on the day of event.', '• Starting time to upload videos : 11 am on 20 Feb 2025 (after the stalls open at 10 am)• Counting day : 2.30 pm on 21 Feb 2025• Individual Participation.• Participants will be judged based on the script, voice over content, positioning, creativity and originality of the video. Number of likes will also be considered as secondary criteria. Judges decision is final. Fake account likes are strictly condemnable.• More weightage will be given for the quality of the content. Judges decision is final. More likes may lead to winning chances.• The number of likes will be counted sharply at the end of the time period given. The final decision will be based on the system settings of the host. As the counting of all the participants will take some time, the coordinators are not responsible for the last minute addition of likes. The participants should accept the judgement and should not raise any objections. To avoid this, the participants are requested to keep the likes really high, so that others cannot reach you in that short span during final counting.• The judgement of the event is totally unbiased. All the rights reserved with the coordinators. Any argument / violation of rule will lead to disqualification without any justification', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 5, 1),
(92, 'X-Cool Quiz Zone', 'Twist your brain.', 8, 'Hargovan Hadiyal', 9313114826, 0, 100, '2', 3000, 2000, 1500, 'Room No. 201', '21-02-2025', 'There will be several rounds of fun Quiz, based on presence of mind, analytical skills, current affairs etc., there will be an elimination round as first round. If required, there will be elimination after every alternative phase in second round. Rules and conditions will be informed to all participants prior the event.', '• 2 students per group.', '', 'This will be an elimination round.', '', '• Group participation. 2 per group.• There will be several rounds based on general knowledge, analytical and logical reasoning, fun based rounds, etc.,• The judgement of the event is totally unbiased. All the rights reserved with the coordinators. Any argument / violation of rule will lead to disqualification without any justification', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 6, 1),
(93, 'X-One Minute Challenge Zone', 'Challenge Yourself and Have Fun', 8, 'Preksha Rajeshkumar Mehta', 7863048341, 50, 0, '1', 1500, 1000, 500, 'Room No. 201', '21-02-2025', 'Students will be given a fun, adrenaline filled, presence of mind relate tasks to perform in one minute. The evaluation will be based on speed, precision and creativity in performing the tasks under pressure in the given time. Those who complete with maximum output in one minute will be the winner. There will be several rounds to eliminate, in case of more participants. But each round will be interesting', '• Individual participation • One minute challenges will be given to students ( it may be technical, fun, logical etc.,)• The judgement of the event is totally unbiased. All the rights reserved with the coordinators. Any argument / violation of rule will lead to disqualification without any justification', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://drive.google.com/file/d/1A85_XHzhOtikBHuT2sFIwer40kpoqKAK/view?usp=sharing', 'default.jpg', 9999, 5, 1);
